         "html_value": [
            {
               "text": "<p><hr /></p><p><h3>Philosophy</h3>We will begin with the most general definition of philosophy, as mentioned by the <i>Britannica Encyclopædia</i> (<htcite0>):</p><p><ul class=\"citation\"><li><i>\"Philosophy, (from Greek, by way of Latin, philosophia, “love of wisdom”) the rational, abstract, and methodical consideration of reality as a whole or of fundamental dimensions of human existence and experience. Philosophical inquiry is a central element in the intellectual history of many civilizations.\"</i></li> </ul></p><p>Despite this definition, when we speak of philosophy we are not dealing with something closed. We generally speak of different philosophical systems, often separated according to cultures (<htcite1>).</p><p>In this section of <i>History Tracers</i>, we intend to present different philosophical views, which are interconnected with scientific knowledge, in order to show distinct perspectives — which are not wrong for being different — and that help to explain what we experience.</p>",
